[normal]Housing[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]services[bold]UNISON has tens of thousands of members employed by housing associations, providing social housing to those in need and often providing social care to the tenants as well. 
[normal]Austerity 
[normal]has reduced house building with a
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]63%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]cut in capital financing available for new social housing
[normal]73%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]report more tenants are falling behind with their rent
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]35%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]said the top reason was the bedroom tax. The next most common reasons were:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]– complex benefit c
[normal]hanges
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]– the rising cost of living
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]– under-employment and un-employment
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]– financial hardship.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]50%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]have seen an increase in tenants being evicted or forced to move because of financial pressures
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]37%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]have seen a reduction in non-statutory services (such
[normal] as play schemes and community centres)
[normal]58%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]report more debt management advisors being employed by their housing
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]associations                                                    
[normal] 43%[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]report a rise in anti-social behaviour from tenants
